   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON ELEVEN THE SENSE OF LIFE Scripture Reading: Rom 8:6, 2, 11; Eph 4:18-19; Heb 8:10; 1 John 2:27; John 15:4-5; Phil 2:13 OUTLINE The meaning of the sense of life: The feeling of death weakness, emptiness, uneasiness, restlessness, depression, dryness, darkness, pain, etc. on the negative side Rom 8:6a.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The feeling of life and peace strength, satisfaction, peace, rest, release, liveliness, watering, brightness, comfort, etc. on the positive side Rom 8:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Related to the consciousness of the conscience Eph 4:19.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The source of the sense of life: The divine life with the richest, strongest, and keenest feeling Eph 4:18.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The law of life the natural ability and function of life Rom 8:2; Heb 8:10.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Holy Spirit the anointing ointment Rom 8:11; 1 John 2:27.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Christ abiding in us John 15:4-5.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God operating in us Phil 2:13.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The function of the sense of life: Making us know whether we are living in the natural life or in the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Making us know whether we are living in the flesh or in the spirit.</S>
   </TEXT>
